x4freetext: Heavy water thermal column in PF-K reactor.
Thermal spectrum of Fermi shape, could be described
Cadmium ratio was measured by U-235 ionization chamber
to be 32.0 at the center of the thermal column.
Li(2)CO(3) with graphite powder. For normalization.
Cyclic activation. One cycle time 80 sec.
Reactor reactivity was measured with and without Cd
Ionization boron chamber KNT-52 in paraffin
block of 100 mm diameter. Filled with Ar.
Normalization was done by measurements by Li and C .
